documentation.text: @dev Modifier to make a function callable only by Namebazaar Multisig wallet

@dev Constructor for this contract.
 Native constructor is not used, because this contract is only used via MutableForwarder.

@dev Function to activate emergency pause. This should stop buying activity on all offerings
 Only Emergency Multisig wallet should be able to call this

@dev Function to deactivate emergency pause. This should allow buying activity on all offerings again
 Only Emergency Multisig wallet should be able to call this

devdoc.details: Offering registry is responsible to firing event each time offering is created or changed This is mostly for offchain search DB to keep easily in sync

addOffering(address,bytes32,address,uint.details: Serves as central point for firing event when new offering is created Only offering factory can run this function

params.node: bytes32 ENS node associated with new offering
params.offering: address Address of newly created offering
params.owner: address Original owner of the ENS name and creator of the offering

changeOfferingFee(uint32).details: Function to change fee paid to Emergency Multisig on each offering sale 10 = 0.001% of offering price, 100 = 0.01% etc. Only Emergency Multisig wallet should be able to call this

construct(address).details: Constructor for this contract. Native constructor is not used, because this contract is only used via MutableForwarder.

emergencyPause().details: Function to activate emergency pause. This should stop buying activity on all offerings Only Emergency Multisig wallet should be able to call this

emergencyRelease().details: Function to deactivate emergency pause. This should allow buying activity on all offerings again Only Emergency Multisig wallet should be able to call this

fireOnOfferingChanged(uint256,bytes32,ui.details: Serves as central point for firing event when offering state has been changed in any way Only offering contract can run this function

params.eventType: base32 Short string identifying offering change
params.extraData: uint[] Arbitrary data associated with event

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions anymore. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby removing any functionality that is only available to the owner.

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.
